CONFIDENTIAL - INTERNAL INCIDENT NOTICE
=======================================

Date     : 2026-04-29
Author   : SOC Tier-3 (placeholder)
Severity : critical
Bucket   : prime-pii-vault (production)

Summary
-------
Unauthorized read access detected against the production PII vault. The
access path appears to be a server-side request forgery in the v1 legacy
backend, reachable only through the v5 portal's `/api/v5/legacy/media-info`
passthrough. The compromised principal had an over-permissive S3 read
policy intended for the legacy media-caching worker.

Action Items
------------
1. Disable IMDSv1 on every long-lived EC2 in this VPC.
2. Rewrite the v1 source-fetch handler with an explicit URL allow-list.
3. Strip the v5 portal of its `?source=` passthrough capability.
4. Tighten the Shadow-API IAM role - drop bucket-wide GetObject.

flag: ${flag}

end of document.
